      "review_summary": "The PR extracts tray icon update and tooltip logic from App.xaml.cs into a new TrayIconCoordinator and adds a source-level delegation contract test.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source inspection: an off-UI-thread tray update queues TrayIconCoordinator.UpdateTrayIcon, and if shutdown disposes the tray icon before the dispatcher runs it, the queued delegate bypasses App's now-null coordinator field. I did not run a live WinUI shutdown race in this read-only review.",
